ANTHRAX - KAZAKHSTAN (06): (QOSTANAY) CATTLE, RECURRENCE
********************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

[1]
Date: Thu 11 Nov 2021
Source: KazNews [in Russian, machine trans., edited]
https://time.kz/news/society/2021/11/11/karantin-ustanovili-iz-za-novoj-vspyshki-sibirskoj-yazvy-v-kostanajskoj-oblasti


Quarantine was established due to a new outbreak of anthrax in the Kostanay region, the [KazTAG] agency reports.

"Quarantine has been established on the property of Batalinskoye LLP, Zhaltyrkol village, Arkhangelsk rural district, Denisov district, Kostanay region, due to the occurrence of cattle anthrax disease," said the statement from the akimat [district administration] of the rural district.

Previously on 13 Jul 2021, KazTAG reported that quarantine was introduced due to an outbreak of anthrax in the Kostanay region. On the same day [13 Jul 2021], it became known that 3 people were infected with the disease.

Anthrax is a particularly dangerous infectious disease in livestock and wild animals of all types, as well as humans, often leading to the death of the sick person in the very first days of infection.

--
