******
[2]
Date: Thu 11 Nov 2021
Source: Nasha Gazeta [in Russian, machine trans., edited]
https://www.ng.kz/modules/news/article.php?storyid=43725


An anthrax case in a head of cattle was reported in the village of Zhaltyrkol, Kostanay region, Agroqogam.kz reports. Accordingly, the forced slaughter of the animal was carried out in the property of Batalinskoye LLP. In total, there were 166 head of cattle involved in the outbreak.

By the decision of the akim [administrator] of the Arkhangelsk rural district, quarantine was introduced on the farm, which, presumably, will be lifted next week.

"The fact was revealed on [26 Oct 2021]. There are no livestock deaths [at that time]. The situation is now stable. As it should be, disinfection was carried out, "said Akat Shektybaev, head of the veterinary department of the akimat of Kostanay region.

--
